                <head>No. 413.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Marsh</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-11-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 18, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 749.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge with thanks the receipt of
                    your No. 922, having reference to the high qualities which distinguished the
                    late Baron Bettino Ricasoli, former prime minister of Italy; as also to his
                    friendship for the United States.</p>
                <p>The estimable qualities of Baron Ricasoli, and his attitude toward this country
                    at a critical period in its history, combine to render his decease a subject of
                    sympathy and regret to the good citizens of the United States.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
